## 1. Executive Summary

This specification defines the implementation of the Agent-Plugin Bus - a bidirectional communication channel that enables real-time modulation of plugin parameters by AI agents, and allows plugins to influence agent behavior. This creates a closed-loop system where agents can "play" the VJ system like an instrument.

**Critical Objectives:**
- Enable agents to modulate plugin parameters in real-time (<10ms latency)
- Provide a standardized naming convention for agent→plugin bindings
- Allow plugins to read agent state (position, velocity, energy)
- Support bidirectional feedback (plugins can affect agent behavior)
- Maintain 60 FPS sacred rail under all conditions
- Provide clear debugging and visualization tools

